                     <interp inst="t17970111-38-person480" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - Examined by Mr. Fielding. I live in the house of Messrs. Smith, No. 73, <placeName id="t17970111-38-crimeloc238">Lombard-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17970111-38-crimeloc238" type="placeName" value="Lombard-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17970111-38-crimeloc238" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17970111-38-off236 t17970111-38-crimeloc238"></join>.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you remember whether on the 21st of November, any letter arrived, directed to 
               <persName id="t17970111-38-person481">
                  Nicholas
                   Vansitart
               <interp inst="t17970111-38-person481" type="surname" value="Vansitart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970111-38-person481" type="given" value="Nicholas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970111-38-person481" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Esq.? - A. No; there was not.</p>
               <p>Q. Nor any containing bills, remittances from Stokesley? - A. None at all.</p>
               <p>Q. Be so good as favour me with the firm of<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179701110057"></xptr>your house? - A. 
               <persName id="t17970111-38-person482">
                  Samuel
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17970111-38-person482" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
